=head1 DESCRIPTION

In a CreateResolverRule
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/Route53/latest/APIReference/API_route53resolver_CreateResolverRule.html)
request, an array of the IPs that you want to forward DNS queries to.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Ip => Str

One IPv4 address that you want to forward DNS queries to.


=head2 Ipv6 => Str

One IPv6 address that you want to forward DNS queries to.


=head2 Port => Int

The port at C<Ip> that you want to forward DNS queries to.


=head2 Protocol => Str

The protocols for the target address. The protocol you choose needs to
be supported by the outbound endpoint of the Resolver rule.


=head2 ServerNameIndication => Str

The Server Name Indication of the DoH server that you want to forward
queries to. This is only used if the Protocol of the C<TargetAddress>
is C<DoH>.



